<unit id="8ae8aefa-8618-4731-a4f2-770da977f723">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 2</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: # </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Custom Notifications #</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e2972681-d611-41da-8bb0-f972bf2cacca">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 3</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: *	</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Authors: José Fischer, Noelia Ruiz Martínez</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="6d83e83f-37bd-4966-b05b-edf7285b4dca">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 5</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>This add-on is used to customize toast notifications.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="8e6fb5c1-976c-4f36-a424-91816a527be6">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 7</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can choose to read the whole notification or just the application which sends it, and if notifications will be spoken, displayed in braille or both.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="e872555c-ec0b-4ffd-91e6-50bb15e4c3c7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 9</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Settings ##</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="7ff3bea7-b64a-486b-bf27-8b3a2b37ebcf">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 11</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Go to NVDA's menu, Preferences submenu, Settings, and select the Custom Notifications category. There you'll find the following controls:</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="1eeaef60-cd10-429e-8d6d-f57cada73a63">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 13</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A checkbox to choose if notifications should be truncated, checked by default.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="da780634-a746-4cc8-bcc9-fab1f97bf252">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 14</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>An edit box to set the start limit of notifications, empty by default.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="fa71cd86-4df6-4826-a46d-eac93d8884c0">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 15</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>An edit box to set the end limit of notifications, ", " (comma space) by default.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="ecbb1c67-447c-4948-a18b-f03d1e515fd9">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 16</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>A list of checkboxes to select if notifications should be spoken and displayed in braille, both checked by default.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="b21b6617-97f4-42fc-b591-44088ed41080">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 17</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>An edit box to type a text to send a test notification, to get an idea of how NVDA will present toasts.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="d4d03f1a-928a-427c-b785-b12a29433db7">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 18</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>If the previous edit box contains text, a button to send a notification, so you can test if your selected  settings work fine for you.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="789732e8-e4f2-48f2-a76b-a26e911ce133">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 20</note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>You can assign a gesture to open the add-on settings panel, and to toggle various add-on settings, from NVDA's menu, Preferences submenu, Input gestures dialog, Configuration category.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="f4b8b486-6204-4bc1-aeb7-69c8e6dea8fd">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 22</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: ## </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>Changes for 2.0.0 ##</source>
</segment>
</unit>
<unit id="fc56f97c-0790-4290-b457-7aecc81b7e4a">
<notes>
<note appliesTo="source">line: 24</note>
<note appliesTo="source">prefix: * </note>
</notes>
<segment>
<source>In the add-on settings panel, added an edit box to set the start limit of notifications.</source>
</segment>
</unit>
